FBIS4-16263 "drsov073_i_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-073 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 CENTRAL ASIA Kazakhstan Nazarbayev Separates Presidential, Government Staff Nazarbayev Separates Presidential, Government Staff LD1504101494 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0800 GMT 15 Apr 94 LD1504101494 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network Kazakh BFN [Text] The president of Kazakhstan has issued a decree on reorganizing the staff of the Republic's president and council of ministers. The decree says, in part: The existing staff of the president and the cabinet of ministers should be reorganized by being divided into the staff of the president and the administration of the council of ministers of the Republic of Kazakhstan. Those made redundant from the staff of the president and the council of ministers will be given social guarantees and compensation in conformity with the Labor Code.
